<br>
Halloumi is made from sheep or goat's milk, and is a good source of calcium. Arugula contains plenty of folate, and tomatoes will boost your vitamin C intake. </a>.<br>
<br>
<b>Ingredients</b>
<br><div class="mobileAdPlacement"></div>
<ul><li> 1 Tbsp. olive oil </li><li> 100g halloumi cheese </li><li>2 slices thick-cut whole grain or sourdough bread</li><li>1 Tbsp. mayonnaise</li><li>½ tomato, thinly sliced</li><li>1 cup fresh arugula</li><li>Salt and pepper</li></ul><br>
<b>Preparation time:</b> 20 minutes<br>
<br>
<b>Steps:</b>
<br><div class="teadsAdPlacement"></div>
1. Drizzle the oil into a non-stick frying pan and set over medium heat.<br>
2. Slice the halloumi into ½-inch thick pieces, and place in the frying pan to cook. The cheese will release some liquid, and then begin to brown. Cook for 5 minutes and when the bottom is golden brown flip the cheese over and cook the other side for a minute or two. <br>
3. While the cheese is cooking, spread the mayonnaise over both slices of bread. Top one slice with the tomato slices and arugula and season with salt and pepper.<br>
4. When the cheese is golden, place it on top of the arugula. Cover with the second slice of bread, placing it mayonnaise-side down, slice in half and eat immediately. 
